album.title: Music From The Doerfel-Verse
album.description:
Welcome to our Music feed! Want to hear the stories behind the songs, live jams, Doerfel-gossip, and who knows what else from our Doerfel-Vault? You can, and it's free! Just subscribe in a podcasting 2.0 app!

We don't make money from streams and there are no ads. We want to share music we love making. We just ask if you find any value, to return whatever it's worth to you with time, talent, or treasure. - The Doerfels

tracks.title: Angel Beast
tracks.summary:
Music written by The Doerfels and Miles Fonda.
Miles split is set up to go to A wallet for his son Kaden.
Lyrics by Miles Fonda: 

Which one is an angel,
Which one’s a beast?
Which one has the blessed hope,
And which wants a feast?

But if one must be a blessing
And one must be a curse
Then why does injury heal stronger
But a happy heart hurt worse?

They say that life is like a mountain
With a valley in its shade
But the snow is never greener on the peak
Than grass down in the glades
Though the stony top is higher
And the view is always clear
It’s the dirty valley peasants drinking beer
That lose their mountain climbing fear

Which one is a steeple
Which one’s a jail?
Which one gives you hope today
And which one reads your mail?

But if one must be a blessing 
And one must be a due
Then why do prisoners reform themselves
But church parishioners never do?

They say that life is like a mountain
With a valley in its shade
But the snow is never greener on the peak
Than the grass in the glades
Though the stony top is higher
And the view is always clear
It’s the dirty valley peasants drinking beer
That lose their mountain climbing fear

BRIDGE
Time is not two hands on a clock
Beating like the heartbeat of a fawn
The sun goes down, the sun comes up
Its dusk, and now its dawn
We keep track on our fingers
Like we used to do in school
Hopeless has two syllables
And so does “pain” with ‘you’

You lay asleep at night and cry
Because it always has an end
Just like a play, intermission’s here,
The viewers now must fend.

They say that life is like a mountain
With a valley in its shade
But the snow is never greener on the peak
Than the grass in the glades
Though the stony top is higher
And the view is always clear
It’s the dirty valley peasants drinking beer
That lose their mountain climbing fear

Pray tell me, what here is the present time
And which memory was you?
Which one gives you sustenance
And which one takes your food?

If one must be a blessing
And one must be the past
Then why won’t memories leave us
Yet the present time runs fast?

END(not in recording but written by Miles)
I will not lie, life is not an angel
Yet life is not simply a beast
Both rely on one another
Like a loaf of bread needs yeast.

tracks.title: METAL IN THE BANJO
tracks.subtitle: METAL IN THE BANJO
tracks.summary:
METAL IN THE BANJO by TJ Doerfel(Sir TJ The Wrathful)
I made this song for Sir Libre after somehow it came up in discussion that I should make a metal banjo song. It took on it's own sound, not exactly metal, but close enough. However, after over 25 hours of creating and producing it, my Macbook with all the projects files, it's hard drive died. I was unable to recover the project or anything else on it and after trying to remove the HD, smashed it with a hammer with wrath. I had saved a few semi-mixed versions, and decided to move forward and release it. 
Fun fact: 5 string banjos are surprisingly heavy, coming in at around 12 pounds. It's because other than the neck, it has a lot of metal pecies that help make up its tone.

album.title: 18 Sundays
album.description:
A bunch of best friends who grew up in the Buffalo, NY area making music throughout our childhood and teenage years. From left to right: Eddy, TJ, Kim, Bethany, Miles, Ethan. These songs were written by us from approximately 2003 to 2005. Think of this album as audio lore for early Doerfel/Fonda-verse music! 

Miles fronted much of the songwriting and arrangements of these songs, and I(TJ) felt this would be a fun album to release in Miles' honor. While I love ALL these songs, "Ode to Ashley" really captured the joy Miles and I had making music together. Thanks Ashley!

We didn't have autotune back then, but there is something beautiful about the rawness of these tracks. Until we get to jam again in heaven, we love and miss you Miles, and may your music live on forever!
------------
Miles Fonda(4/15/88 to 1/21/23) - Drums, lead vocals.
Bethany Fonda - Lead and backing vocals.
Kim Doerfel - Lead and backing vocals, fiddle.
TJ Doerfel - Guitars.
Eddy Doerfel - Bass and mandolin.
Ethan Fonda - percussion and band jester.

To see what everyone is up to now check out https://www.doerfelverse.com and https://www.bethanyfonda.com/

Miles' splits go to his son Kaden.
Special thanks to our parents(Ralph and Tamala Fonda, Tom and Cheryl Doerfel) for helping us on our musical journey.

album.title: Generation Gap
album.description:
Doug Yeomans is a Buffalo NY guitar legend. In 2009 when Ben Doerfel was 13 years old, Doug thought it would be cool to capture this time in a recording. Can you pick out the veteran from the 13 year old as they pick through these old traditional tunes? Doug is now part of the family as Ben married Dougs daughter, Emma in 2020. Anyways, I Hope you enjoy this magical album I had the honor of recording -  Sir TJ The Wrathful

I can't wait until we get to write more songs together again, utill then, I will always treasure what he left us, and maybe some of you will too :)

tracks.title: They Don't Know
tracks.summary:
We picked this song to release on Episode 4 of our podcast, "Into The Doerfel-verse" If you find any value in this song, please let us know!

Notice the instruments in the song art. Our friend Jim Stoneman made us hockey sticks guitars which we would play a few songs on every show. All us Doerfel boys wanted to play hockey when we grew up, instead we turned into wimpy musicians! We still enjoy hitting the ice from time to time.

album.title: deathdreams
album.description:
'deathdreams' was written and performed by Emily Whitehurst, the solo artist behind Survival Guide. Produced and recorded by Bob Hoag in late 2022 at Flying Blanket Studios in Mesa, AZ.

At times a darkly sonic and emotional hand grenade and others a poppy shimmering rainbow of rich melodies and textures, 'deathdreams' is a tour de force that showcases the depth of Whitehurst’s songwriting, lyrical imagery, and vocal fortitude. Far-ranging in its topic matter, the album touches on the themes of anxiety, the power of cinema, and the dangers of societal influences, in addition to Whitehurst’s dreams about dying.

tracks.title: Bad Little Seed
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

Place cards, centerpiece
She asks me what she did wrong
How disappointing
Gave it away for a song
Sticky floor, sticky beer
Smells like cigarettes here
Surrounded by dirty men
And I’d do it all again

Get out of this town and see the world
Take your life and do what you prefer
Get out of this town, go see the world
Breaking the rules and your heart
How did us girls ever turn out this way?
Breaking the rules and your heart

You gave us courage, you gave us strength
You taught us girls can do anything
We don’t have to wear the white dress standing at the altar
If we don’t want to now
Do you regret it all?
Wish you’d kept your words small?
I’m on my own road
Where it ends up, I don’t know

CHORUS

Joy won’t shelter you
You can’t eat your dreams
What a bad little seed
Who just wanted to be free

CHORUS

tracks.title: Sour Sorrow
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

It’s so embarrassing to admit that I still feel sick
When our song comes on the radio
Flavor’s bitter like vinegar but you’ve been with her
For ages now, I know
I’m so tired of pining over you
If there was something I could do, I would do it

Parting is such sour sorrow
The taste you left with me
It’s a real tough pill to swallow
So hard to believe that it’s just 
Sour sorrow
Sour sorrow, now it’s just
Sour sorrow
When will this feeling leave?

I used to think I was oh so strong
I was never wrong
Never let a man get me down
Salty memories make my skin burn
When will I learn to forget you now?
I’m so ashamed that I can’t be happy for you
If there was something I could do, I could do, I would do, I would do it

CHORUS

I told myself so long ago
Not to count on another soul
You tore my lungs out and let them go cold
There’s no use in saying it now

‘Cause parting is such sour sorrow
You meant the world to me
When we used to put on our show
Part of me believed 

CHORUS

tracks.title: Pie
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

You are me and I was you
You think I’m glaring but it’s not true
Even if you just appeared, you’ve always been a piece of me
Same cloth, same blood, same tree
Same feet stomping rhythm with our stories

Let me bubblewrap you
Hide you from his eyes
I just wanna get you through these dangerous times
Pull you through the fire to the other side

You look like a fresh-baked pie
Their tongues are hanging out
Never forget that your machine gun is your mouth
Little sister, don’t you doubt, oh

I know you hate it when I tell you what to do
But it’s only because I worry they’ll steal the light from you

Just let me bubblewrap you
Hide you from his eyes
It gets me twisted up inside
To see you as a prize

CHORUS

Oh, fresh-baked pie

CHORUS

tracks.title: Blood Perfume
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

All you gotta do is believe me
I love the way that you trust me
I love the way you put none above me
It’s your turn, prove that you love me
My words become your scriptures
Got the best evidential pictures
I know you better than you
Do you know how much I protect you?

You can’t say no to the brightest teeth in the room
You can’t say no when I slip a little bit of your blood
Into my perfume
Into my perfume
Just a little bit
Into my perfume
A bit of your blood

You wake, first thing wanna see me
I make it so easy
Just kneel and kiss my feetsies
That’s all you gotta do to appease me
So go and play the part now
I’ll allow you to feel smart now
You think it’s your decision
As you execute my vision

CHORUS

I will keep you safe
If you take my hand
Do not look away
Give me all you have

CHORUS

tracks.title: Sharpshooter
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

Looking at the clock
Telling me I can’t stop
I don’t deserve the rest yet
Continue on the quest
Did some things I can’t forget
I lay down only to charge, I got lucky stars
In the middle of the night
In the dark and quiet
Wishing I never had to slumber
I am always under the spell of the beam

What happens if I get there?
Will I dissolve into thin air?
Sharpshooter
What’s there to run from when it’s 
All inside your head?
Sharpshooter

Every day is a sigh
Looking forward in time 
Looking for the next chance to ride the avalanche
Or hitching on thunder
Wishing that I never had to slumber
I am always under the spell of the beam

CHORUS

Only the dead truly sleep
No wheels to keep turning, no grinding of the teeth
Only the dead truly sleep
They’re free from the power of the magnetic beam

CHORUS

tracks.title: Lady Neptune
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

She comes between us
But we can’t see it
Scratching with pins and needles
Saying the perfect words
Up overhead the vultures circle
We’re still a bit too fresh but
They won’t be waiting long

I can save us all if I die before I wake
Pray it’s not all a mistake as I go under
Soak me to the bone
No one showed me how, but now I know
I’m going under

What did we think was gonna happen?
When she crashed the party
No one told her she had to go
I don’t want to do it 
But I know I’ve got to prove it
So here goes
I will fall into it and let go

CHORUS

Too late to turn around
My fate is floating down
And I’ll sink into the cold and dark
And I feel the slowing of my heart yeah
But when I rise, tear her world apart, oooh

CHORUS

tracks.title: wordswordswords
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

Is this the lion’s curse?
Solid gold your wordswordswords
Oh so many to rehearse
If I want to keep my head

(Why do I always feel like I’m on the brink)

Living in my house of cards
Thank my lucky stars there’s no breeze today
Burn me at the stake in town
I’m on shaky ground
There is only one way

Overpowered by my heartbeat
Drills in deep just like a cavity
Wordswordswords, smell of gasoline
Sound like buzzing bees

Can we put the petals back on the rose?
Don’t cut the thorns off, we need those too
Let’s remind ourselves that everybody hurts
And no one knows what we’re doing on this earth

Ten thousand eyes become one
Damage is done
I start to decompose
Threw myself upon the tracks
There’s no going back, every surface cold

Overpowered by my heartbeat
Drills in deep just like a cavity
Wordswordswords, smell of gasoline
Light the match for me

tracks.title: Fight Me
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

I’m not here to judge or challenge anyone
In fact I’m leaving out the back door
I can’t just choose a color
I don’t play well with others
Please don’t give me the score

We’ve got no spirit
We don’t wanna hear it
You may think I’m not alive
We’ve got no spirit
Can’t you hear it in my voice
And see it in my glassy eyes?

First it’s head to head, then eye for an eye
And they’re saying that it’s healthy
It seems very human
So I’m just assuming
There’s something wrong with my circuitry

CHORUS

Please don’t call my name
I’ll only let you down
Looking across the way

To some I’m just a void
A heart with a hole
And my temperature is icy
I get it on the surface
But what’s the real purpose?
Seeing red’s never fun for me

CHORUS

tracks.title: Don't Feel Bad
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

Who picks up smoking cigarettes as a full-grown man?
So much so that it changes the color of his hand
As the sun shines all around him, he stews into rage
Shoving glass into his chest while shooting arrows of blame

You took advantage of the chances that I gave you
2nd turned to 7th, and the 8th time I forbade you

Don’t feel bad, cause he hates everything anyway
He hates everyone anyway, and especially me
Don’t feel bad, cause he hates everything anyway
He hates everyone anyway, and especially me

Her downy comforter is soaked in red red wine
The heavy weight drowns out her ghosts, but it blocks any light
As she opens up her mouth, poison pearls start to drop
And a scoop of frozen guilt is the cherry on top

CHORUS

tracks.title: Stay Dead
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

There’s a living ghost that’s haunting me
He doesn’t even know I can plainly see
I don’t drudge up the dead
Leave ‘em instead
Keeping all the stories straight in my head, no
Tries so hard, but I’ll always be free

I’m the statue and you’re the rain
Tears coming down my face, but my eyes look the same
And you can’t make me scream, oh no
And you can’t make me scream, oh no no no

Like a wind-up toy stuck on its side
You think you work so hard, but all you really do is lie
You’re setting me a trap
Guessing I’ll snap
Crawling on the floor, waiting for my scraps, yeah
I just watch as the fake blood dries

CHORUS

He thinks pushing me will bring us back together
But that world is gone forever, gone forever
And you can’t make me scream, oh no
And you can’t make me scream, no no
Never ever

CHORUS

tracks.title: I'll Picture You
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

I really hoped for the double decker bus
Though we never made it back to London anyway
Maybe even better Mount Vesuvius
Positioned into a permanent embrace

I was wrong to think that as the red slowed
I’d have your hand to hold, both our fingers growing cold
But somehow when I focus on your face
Dark fear’s erased
Whatever takes me to the next place is love

I’m about to die, so I picture you
About to die knowing our love is true
Maybe if I love hard enough, I’ll get to stay here by your side
So I’ll picture you when I die

Can you sense it?
Are my thoughts breaking through to your sleepy head
Can you feel it?
Is there anything we left unsaid?

Looking down at the city lights below
Time is slowing down, but only for me
Nothing special about the concrete curve
My vision blurred until your eyes are all I see

I was wrong to think that as the red slowed
I wouldn’t do it all alone
Feel a hum within my bones
But somehow when I focus on your face
I float in space
Whoever takes me to the next place is love

CHORUS

album.summary:
'deathdreams' was written and performed by Emily Whitehurst, the solo artist behind Survival Guide. Produced and recorded by Bob Hoag in late 2022 at Flying Blanket Studios in Mesa, AZ.

At times a darkly sonic and emotional hand grenade and others a poppy shimmering rainbow of rich melodies and textures, 'deathdreams' is a tour de force that showcases the depth of Whitehurst’s songwriting, lyrical imagery, and vocal fortitude. Far-ranging in its topic matter, the album touches on the themes of anxiety, the power of cinema, and the dangers of societal influences, in addition to Whitehurst’s dreams about dying.

album.title: The First Five Years
album.description:
‘Joe Martin - The First Five Years’ brings together a body of work that starts with the Small World EP, released in 2017, to songs from Joe’s debut studio album and everything in between. The stories, best encapsulated by this live album, (acoustically and stripped back the way they were originally conceived and written) take the listener on a journey lived through Joe’s eyes. From the US state-roaming anecdotes of ‘Denver’ to the stargazing, space traveling tale of ‘Daddy Gene’, Joe’s unique blend of UK and US influences are best heard in this live setting.

One man, his guitar and his stories of the first five years!

To get a limited physical copy, visit https://www.joemartinmusic.com/merch

album.title: Daddy Gene
album.description: The story behind this song comes from a documentary film called 'The Last Man On The Moon', where astronaut Eugene Cernan travels to the moon as part of Apollo 17. At the time, he travelled further than anyone has ever been, and has still to this day travelled faster than anyone has ever been as part of the Apollo 10 mission. He promised his young daughter Tracy that he'd bring her back a moonbeam and wrote her initials in the lunar dust. I was so inspired by the magic of this story, that this song came very quickly and easily. Written from the perspective of Tracy about her dad, wondering if he was going to make it home safe.

At the time, he travelled further than anyone has ever been, and has still to this day travelled faster than anyone has ever been as part of the Apollo 10 mission. He promised his young daughter Tracy that he'd bring her back a moonbeam and wrote her initials in the lunar dust. I was so inspired by the magic of this story, that this song came very quickly and easily. Written from the perspective of Tracy about her dad, wondering if he was going to make it home safe.

album.title: Wild and Free
album.description: This debut EP released in 2021 was an experiment of music creation, recording, and production. With a bit of this and a bit of that, the end product amped up Anni's singer-songwriter style to full production pop-rock with notes of jazz. Anni wrote the music and lyrics and performed the vocals, piano and synth. Kristopher Ewaniuk produced, mixed & mastered, and added guitar and bass. Anni's sister Vicki played drums, brass by Rachel Ewaniuk, and back up vocals by Anni's husband, Toby, and friends Chelsea Lyn Meyer and Mike Geroni. The album cover was created by the talented artist, Erin Powell. Check out her artwork here: http://ginsengalley.com/

tracks.title: Blue Heron Pink Flamingo
tracks.summary:
Blue Heron - the cool bird that is so often hanging out at the creek. What a good Pennsylvania bird. And quite the singing voice! 

Pink Flamingo - the pink bird on the cans of Natural Lite "Naturdays" that my friend Billy and picked up on our pizza shop break to sip on while in the studio recording with Chelsea Lyn Meyer. 

Just felt like putting them in a song together.

tracks.title: Where There's a Will There's a Way
tracks.summary:
I really was learning how to write with my other hand at the time. I had wrist pain in my dominant hand and was giving it a rest.

My mom did always say "Can't means won't" a lot too. That stuck with me. 


Learning to write with my other hand
If I think I most certainly can
Mom always said, "can't mean's won't"
Why go about it same old same old?
As above, so  below
Mind will make what the heart sows

The sun is out behind the clouds
It's always clear
Who we need will always appear
Passion is key fly with the dove
A wise man travels with a compass of love

Go on ahead and rock the boat
Go on ahead and rock the boat
Go on ahead and rock the boat, OH!

This feeling inside is so hard to hide
And my heart has so much to say
Making my way at the end of the day
Where there's a will there's a way
Where there's a will there's a way
Where there's a will there's a way
Where there's a will there's a way

Lalalas...

tracks.title: Wild and Free
tracks.summary:
The title and song were inspired by a rear-mirror car ornament my talented sister-in-law, Erin, made for me. She's a fabulous artist!!! Check her out at http://ginsengalley.com/ or 
Erin also designed the Wild and Free album cover.

Distraction is there
At every turn
Dissonance, with some, you know
Everyone's a critic
Turn away, stay the course
And I'm my own worst critic
And the hardest to ignore

Watch me as I chase the light
The dream I had since I was a child
The secret to live wild and free
Be one with the one inside of me
Watch  me as I free the bind
And lift the weight and run like wild
The secret is be one with all
And live the dream
And love it all

First row seat
And I watch my life unfold
Head in Heaven, feet on the Earth

Of the greatest lessons I have learned
Practice hard, the Golden Rule
And give it all I have to give
and Love flows in return

Watch me as I chase the light
The dream I had since I was a child
The secret to live wild and free
Be one with the one inside of me
Watch  me as I free the bind
And lift the weight and run like wild
The secret is be one with all
And live the dream
And love it all

Shoo-be-doo-wop...

tracks.title: Dance With Me
tracks.summary:
This song was inspired by the Wine and Jazz Fest that my husband and I used to go for a few years in a row. It was so much fun wandering around and dancing in the great outdoors while listening to talented jazz artists, and sipping our wine from the tasting tents. It was a special time. We got engaged there in June 2013 and were married in October. 

Dance with me
Oh dance with me
Dance with me
Oh dance with me
Taste the wine on my lips
wrap your arms round my hips
let's sway, let's sway, let's sway, let's sway

Move like this
Bend and dip
Move like this
Bend and dip
Taste the wine on my lips
wrap your arms round my hips
let's sway, let's sway, let's sway, let's sway

Hold me close
Give it a go
Hold me so close
Give it ago
Taste the wine on my lips
wrap your arms round my hips
let's sway, let's sway, let's sway, let's sway

Dance with me
Oh dance with me
Dance with me
Oh dance with me
Taste the wine on my lips
wrap your arms round my hips
let's sway, let's sway, let's sway, let's sway
uh huh, uh huh...

tracks.title: Friends
tracks.summary:
Inspiration for this song came from being in two weddings in one day. One for two of my good friends from high school, and the other for my sister-in-law and brother-in-law. What a day! It was awesome. It went so smoothly, with little coordination and intervention on my part. One wedding happened to be earlier in the day, the other later, and I was able to wear the same dress to both since the brides chose the same color. It was meant to be all the way around. I was reflecting on how many beautiful, loving, people I am blessed to know and have known in my life, and just how many circles of family and friends I got to see all in one day!

Somehow I came to find you
I guess it was part of the plan
I'm glad I got to know you
I'm thankful you're my friend
Angel walking Earth
So much I have to learn
Hold my hand and walk with my, I'm listening
And oh,

If I never met you
I'm not sure where I'd be 
Little did you know, you came to rescue me
Whether in the good times, or whether in the bad
You helped create me, to make me who I am

People come and go
And some I haven't found
I'll be here with a smile to greet you if you come back around
And when it's time to go
And leave the big blue Earth
I wanna be somebody's angel
Be with them, birth to birth

If I never met you
I'm not sure where I'd be 
Little did you know, you came to rescue me
Whether in the good times, or whether in the bad
You helped create me, to make me who I am

We all make mistakes
We all lose control
Some much like each other
Forgive, look past it all

If I never met you
I'm not sure where I'd be 
Little did you know, you came to rescue me
Whether in the good times, or whether in the bad
You helped create me, to make me who I am

tracks.title: Rewinding the Future HCPP24
tracks.summary:
Talk presented at Hacker’s Congress Paralelní Polis on 5.10.24.Rewinding the Future: The Cultural Anarchism of CassettesAbstractCypherpunks rejoice! We finally have a private, anonymous, and censorship resistant media: the compact cassette. Historically, cassettes have toppled governments, sparked moral panics, and spread subversive messages. But are they still relevant today besides hipster nostalgia? Join me as I recount the transformative history of cassettes, uncovering the parallel societies they have built and explore their modern applications.In today’s age of pervasive surveillance, the portable, offline, and analog nature of cassettes offers a renewed sense of relevance and freedom. I’ll cover cypherpunk applications of cassettes including innovative uses in backups, ecash, steganography, and analog and digital encryption. And just for fun, you will learn how to make tape loops and DIY sound on sound recording as well. So, get ready to press record and learn how analog recording can aid us in the fight for self-sovereignty and freedom.Call 1-877-BIT-LOFI and leave crazy messages on a real cassette!How to get a physical tape:Mail a postcard with your return address to

album.description:
Love In Its Purest Form is an audial onslaught of ethereal, synthesized, alternative, nocturnal melodies from the inner depths of your dreams, nightmares, realities and higher consciousness.

Written in my college dorm room and recorded between 2021 and 2023 through many trials and tribulations.
credits
released November 25, 2023

All sounds and lyrics written and recorded by Vance Latta.
Additional drum input provided by Kaden Latta.
Mixed and mastered by Kevin Carafa.

tracks.title: Angel Beast
tracks.summary:
Music written by The Doerfels and Miles Fonda.
Miles split is set up to go to A wallet for his son Kaden.
Lyrics by Miles Fonda: 

Which one is an angel,
Which one’s a beast?
Which one has the blessed hope,
And which wants a feast?

But if one must be a blessing
And one must be a curse
Then why does injury heal stronger
But a happy heart hurt worse?

They say that life is like a mountain
With a valley in its shade
But the snow is never greener on the peak
Than grass down in the glades
Though the stony top is higher
And the view is always clear
It’s the dirty valley peasants drinking beer
That lose their mountain climbing fear

Which one is a steeple
Which one’s a jail?
Which one gives you hope today
And which one reads your mail?

But if one must be a blessing 
And one must be a due
Then why do prisoners reform themselves
But church parishioners never do?

They say that life is like a mountain
With a valley in its shade
But the snow is never greener on the peak
Than the grass in the glades
Though the stony top is higher
And the view is always clear
It’s the dirty valley peasants drinking beer
That lose their mountain climbing fear

BRIDGE
Time is not two hands on a clock
Beating like the heartbeat of a fawn
The sun goes down, the sun comes up
Its dusk, and now its dawn
We keep track on our fingers
Like we used to do in school
Hopeless has two syllables
And so does “pain” with ‘you’

You lay asleep at night and cry
Because it always has an end
Just like a play, intermission’s here,
The viewers now must fend.

They say that life is like a mountain
With a valley in its shade
But the snow is never greener on the peak
Than the grass in the glades
Though the stony top is higher
And the view is always clear
It’s the dirty valley peasants drinking beer
That lose their mountain climbing fear

Pray tell me, what here is the present time
And which memory was you?
Which one gives you sustenance
And which one takes your food?

If one must be a blessing
And one must be the past
Then why won’t memories leave us
Yet the present time runs fast?

END(not in recording but written by Miles)
I will not lie, life is not an angel
Yet life is not simply a beast
Both rely on one another
Like a loaf of bread needs yeast.

album.subtitle: Sprouting Symphonies
album.summary:
The Artist primes his canvas. Birds chirp in the distance. The smell of bloom is in the air.
Can you feel it Martha?
The Satellite Spotlight: Sprouting Symphonies draws the magic right in front of your eyes. In a v4v live music showcase The Trusted, Red Arrow Highway, MOOKY, and City Beach make up our tallent for the night. 
The Artist guides you through our spectacle with his tales and poems. As we flip through the pages of our past accounts and create some new ones right in front of you.
Ah yes you. How can we forget to mention your role in this show?
Tonight we ask you to engage in a thing we call Value for Value. What could this mean? That means we have put this production out for your viewing pleasure with zero paywalls nor a single corporate sponsorship. All we ask of you is that you consider adding value back in any way you see fit. This show only holds such magick when those who contribute, choose to reach out and touch it on their own. 
How does one add value?
Time.  Talent. Treasure. You’ve shown up to watch, you’re already contributing value through your time with us. For the next spectacle you could consider joining the team, whether that’s joining our ever growing crew of artists and technicians, or even becoming one of our acts that we showcase. For now though we have a pretty easy way for you to make your mark on these pages…
A Boost. 
What could that be? 
A boost is voluntary payment of bitcoin to the acts, the crew, or the show as a whole.

So You Want To Boost?

This boost is not just a form of value contribution. It’s an interactive experience. When you send in a boost you will see your name and amount appear in the show while also triggering the art we’ve made for you. There is also a scoreboard ledger for the top boosters…not that it’s a competition. Your contribution will forever be immortalized in our live to tape storytale.
The bloom has begun Martha.

feeds.title: True Blue
feeds.description: by Robert Willey (2012).This is the third of my albums in the “blue” series, following “Out of the Blue” (2006) and “Into the Blue” (2007), and like those collections, features a mix of new age experimental bossa nova. It was originally an “enhanced CD”, that is, with two sessions–one to be played in a regular CD player, and another to be read in a computer disk drive, allowing the listener access to liner notes, videos, an interview, lead and lyric sheets, play-along tracks, and links to additional content.

feeds.title: Peace Pieces
feeds.description: by Robert Willey (1993).Hardware:Macintosh SE computerRoland Sound Canvas moduleYamaha KX76 keyboard controllerKorg Wavestation synthesizerMackie 1602 mixerLexicon LXP-1 reverbPanasonic SV-3700 DAT recorderSoftware:Studio Vision (Opcode)Intelligent Music UpBeat (David Zicarelli)Programmable Instruments (Robert Willey)The sounds and processes had a big effect on the musical ideas, textures, and forms. UpBeat was a cool program that was used on half the album's songs. It allowed the user to set boundaries on random events that varied the notes you played, creating variations in drum pitch patterns. I think the fun of working in this environment comes through in the recordings. The era ended...

album.title: Peace Pieces
album.description: by Robert Willey (1993).Hardware:Macintosh SE computerRoland Sound Canvas moduleYamaha KX76 keyboard controllerKorg Wavestation synthesizerMackie 1602 mixerLexicon LXP-1 reverbPanasonic SV-3700 DAT recorderSoftware:Studio Vision (Opcode)Intelligent Music UpBeat (David Zicarelli)Programmable Instruments (Robert Willey)The sounds and processes had a big effect on the musical ideas, textures, and forms. UpBeat was a cool program that was used on half the album's songs. It allowed the user to set boundaries on random events that varied the notes you played, creating variations in drum pitch patterns. I think the fun of working in this environment comes through in the recordings. The era ended when my Macintosh SE's screen finally gave out, since UpBeat was not compatible with new versions of Apple's operating systems. The other important piece of software, Studio Vision also went by the wayside with the demise of Opcode. It had easy-to-construct subsequences that could be linked together, resulting in clear jumps from one texture to another. The computer went out in the trash one day, like my IBM PC-XT did, the one I wrote the first programmable instrument programs on with Rick Bidlack. Apple Macintosh SE computer Yamaha KX76 controller Korg Wavestation keyboard Mackie mixer Roland Sound Canvas tone module Lexicon reverb

tracks.title: Out of the Blue
tracks.summary: In 1993 I released my first CD, entitled "Peace Pieces" as part of a seven-year art/life performance."Out of the Blue" is where my music seems to come from, which I consider more a series of discoveries than compositions. I start with an idea and keep exploring it, paying attention to where it wants to go. Along the way I try to make it sound as I would like to hear it, and to stop before it gets spoiled.Information on the process at http://willshare.com/v4v/album/PeacePieces

feeds.title: The Poet Barfly - Demo
feeds.description: The drunk at the bar next to you is determined to ruin your silent reflection. Their blabbering slowly evolves from jibberish to coherent, and from coherent to brilliant.  They have tapped into exactly what you needed to hear somehow.  An annoyance turned into therapy all because you were too lazy to get up.

feeds.title: Wonder Woman
feeds.description:
"Wonder Woman" is a high-octane, genre-defying anthem that refuses to be boxed in. It’s a fearless blend of country grit, bluegrass twang, and the explosive energy of stadium rock. From the very first strum of an acoustic guitar, the song grabs hold and doesn’t let go. The massive percussion elements, mixed with the raw country and bluegrass instruments, create a sound that’s both grounded and sky-high.
The vocal delivery is raw and unapologetic, matching the intensity of the instrumentation with a fire and grit that makes every line feel like a battle cry. Imagine the roughness of a honk...

album.title: Wonder Woman
album.description:
"Wonder Woman" is a high-octane, genre-defying anthem that refuses to be boxed in. It’s a fearless blend of country grit, bluegrass twang, and the explosive energy of stadium rock. From the very first strum of an acoustic guitar, the song grabs hold and doesn’t let go. The massive percussion elements, mixed with the raw country and bluegrass instruments, create a sound that’s both grounded and sky-high.
The vocal delivery is raw and unapologetic, matching the intensity of the instrumentation with a fire and grit that makes every line feel like a battle cry. Imagine the roughness of a honky-tonk bar and the massive, unrelenting force of a stadium crowd. It’s the sound of crossing boundaries, blending traditions, and turning them up to 11. This song isn’t just heard; it’s felt—a shot of adrenaline, a bold declaration, and a soundtrack for those who never back down.

Doug Yeomans is a Buffalo NY guitar legend. In 2009 when Ben Doerfel was 13 years old, Doug thought it would be cool to capture this time in a recording. I can't wait until we get to write more songs together again, utill then, I will always treasure what he left us, and maybe some of you will too :)

tracks.title: Sensitive Guy
tracks.summary:
Written and performed by Miles Fonda

Sensitive Guy

Its not easy
Being a sensitive guy
Because when you feel your feelings
You can laugh and or maybe cry
I told my coworker that Im afraid to die
I gave my dad a big long hug
And he just rolled his eyes
[spoken] And I’ve never played fantasy football

I’m just a sensitive guy
Trying to make it by
Without getting too depressed
I’m just a sensitive guy
Can sew, bake and make pie
And chick flicks are the best
Lifes to short to hold it in, I might shed a tear right now

Its not easy
Being a sensitive guy
Because when when you show your feelings
It’s impossible to hide
I shout when Jack dies in Titanic every time
Women tell me I’m a nice guy
I use lotion all the time
[spoken] And Ive got The Notebook on my wishlist

Bridge
Weep Weep Weep Weep
Cry Cry Cry Cry
Laugh Laugh Pout Pout
Tears in eyes eyes
Sing sing sing sing
Shout shout shout shout
feel feel care care
Let it all out, out

album.title: Show Me Where They Touched You​.​.​.​Again
album.description:
Volume 2 of the Classics!
Liner notes:
Show me where they touched you...againLoudspeaker- Our first video track with Wax Trax Records. Shut up and Listen! A brash assault on the powers that want to choke us out with the proverbial knee to the neck. We retaliate with our unrelenting and everlasting voices demanding our freedom of speech.PoundSauce- Like someone on a rampage, a drinking anthem that could be our dark take on "Fight for your Right to Party"? This song is simple and minimal with the power and intention of a bull in a china shop. To this day, we love playing this song. This was one of the first original 6 songs that we wrote to open up for Ministry on the Land of Rape and Honey tour, our live debut.I got it made- Another one of those original 6 songs and no one has written one like it since. We enjoyed this song being on "The Texas Chainsaw Massacre...the next generation." The scene where Matthew McConaughey is driving the tow-truck over and over his victim makes for the perfect music video for this track.Regret-The first single on our sophomore release and our only video track for the album What a Mangled Web we Leave. The video featured Michael Jackson's attorney as the clown luring a young Macauley Culkin "looking" kid into our demented Carnaval. The song represented the dark drug induced phase that was my life at the time. Family Values- This track was up for a remix by Ice Cube's producer at the time but the record label went bankrupt right before our European tour with Tool was scheduled. On the bright side,Mike Dean of Geto Boys fame played keyboards on it.Sign the dotted line- Be careful what you wish. The drugs that once fueled my creativity and made up a large part of who I believed I was had now turned into the contract that I had sold my soul for. From the outside looking in, a fun ride through the gutters of a dark mind. Mike Dean plays a sinister riff on the Moog.
Mt Carmel Cookout- The prelude to Ranch Apocalypse, a Texan's view on a Texas debacle. David Koresh inspired followers and caught the attention of many others including our government's ATF. This track sets the tone for the next track. I remember telling Mat Mitchell that he had destroyed my hit by adding the burning babies to this song. Man the drugs were something at the time! Ranch Apocalypse- If you've ever spent a day in Waco you will realize that this was one of many stories that can be told but certainly the most famous. What started as a smart-ass t-shirt turned into 2 songs on the album What a Mangled Web...We Leave. The Branch Davideans and the ATF left a Texas sized brand on Waco and all involved. we just wrote the soundtrack to it.
At War with Myself- Heavy and dark, this track was a self discovery about the destruction and turmoil I had inflicted on myself over many years. The struggle is real and you can bet that there is no surrender when the fight is internal. We are crowded in here and we don't always get along.
Say What You Mean- And mean what you say, I'm not sure of how to say this more clearly. This is one of my favorite tracks on our third album Adult Entertainment for Kids. Featuring Chris Gates of Big Boys and Junkyard fame on guitar. I love playing this song live. It is fun to sing and the message will never die. 
credits
released August 28, 2020

All tracks written and produced by Skatenigs except those credited to Al Jourgensen

album.title: Connector (Overtime Edition)
album.description:
This connects my interest in ambient, textural music with my love of Rock, Blues, Jazz and Soundtrack music. There is still space and mood, but also melodies and rhythm with snappy drums and bass grooves.
It also connects my oldest surviving tracks (I didn’t used to keep much back then, it would just come and go), with my more recent Bonkwave/Not Bonkwave tracks.
All those influences are merged into a coherent picture, vocal guitars going from 50s pop to modern day Chill Hop, folk rock and psychedelic rhythm guitar bleed into ambient textures.
I don’t often make music using anything other than guitar anymore, but when I do this is the sort of thing that comes out.
You can download lossless (higher quality audio) versions of these tracks from my website over here.

tracks.title: Audrey's Kitchen
tracks.summary:
Originally a track for a Bonkwave compilation (Not What I Call Bonkwave Vollume 003), this appears on Bonkcast as a pretend TV Theme tune for the non-existent (in this universe) show called Audrey’s Kitchen:
Often overlooked early 80’s romantic sitcom where Audrey is an American immigrant that runs an East Coast diner with all sort of crazy regulars for breakfast and or brunch. She has a will they/won’t they fractious relationship with the coffee bookshop owner opposite called Mike. Ultimately they will, and then do.

tracks.title: On Open Water
tracks.summary: Track two from the original Connector album.  Very sea-going feel I think.

tracks.title: Palladium City
tracks.summary: Track 3 from Connector, this is actually a reworking/updating of the track Growing Aware which is on Wrecklamation Point, which I remember liking 20-30 years ago but was amazed how slow it sounds now.  But I like the riff, so thought I could improve it.

tracks.title: Arcs in the Sky
tracks.summary: Another update - no existing copies of Bulgarian Mojo survive from 30 years ago and I can’t even remember what this track was called originally, but here it is updated and now in color!

tracks.title: Holden Fruit Gambit
tracks.summary: Because sometimes you need to grab a resonator and pretend you are doing a clock background track for a Schools and Colleges countdown clock.  This is a niche reference, but it has gone well as the start to Bonkwave live launch parties (such as this)!

tracks.title: Raspberry Ripple
tracks.summary: An original for the Connector album.  I was sort of going for a jazz feel morphing into a RATM thing.

tracks.title: Bear Ground Mystery
tracks.summary: Another original for Connector track - I was going for Hank Marvin doing a Satch-type of thing.

tracks.title: Plain
tracks.summary: This one is old but reworked.  My wife’s favourite track I’ve ever done, so I keep playing it for her.

tracks.title: Race You Home
tracks.summary: An old track, not updated because I wouldn’t know how to anymore!  Bit weird  quality because it dates back to when everything had to be overcompressed.  But I think it’s quite sweet, a little nostalgic maybe?

tracks.title: Ropes
tracks.summary: Little SRV quote in here, another one written for Connector to cross the streams…

tracks.title: Disco Transformer
tracks.summary: This track was originally on an Xmas EP that I did instead of cards one year.  Had a picture of Megatron (from the original TV series) wearing a Santa hat.

tracks.title: Vivid Voyage
tracks.summary: Written for Connector, this one is me trying to get a nice balance between ambient texture and actual tune.  Not sure I got it, no longer sure it’s ever possible to merge them, I think I prefer to flip flop between extremes instead of balancing.

tracks.title: It's Not Today
tracks.summary: The last Connector original.  Going for a Bond Theme type of vibe.

tracks.title: Drunk Droids
tracks.summary: This was originally done for an album called The Cherry Book that turned into Connector, so sort of a deleted track thing that I tweaked a bit to include (it might have been two tracks originally?)

tracks.title: Green Lake
tracks.summary:
This is the other book end to Audrey’s Kitchen from the Bonkcast EP (and NWICBW Vol 3 Disc A).
West Coast spin-off from Audrey’s Kitchen where a couple of regulars who were in the police are fired and move to become Private Investigators in Washington State. Not very successful because of the weird tonal changes between sit-com and dark crime. This might have influenced both Frasier and Twin Peaks, which gives you an idea of the ground they were attempting to cover.

album.summary:
This connects my interest in ambient, textural music with my love of Rock, Blues, Jazz and Soundtrack music. There is still space and mood, but also melodies and rhythm with snappy drums and bass grooves.
It also connects my oldest surviving tracks (I didn’t used to keep much back then, it would just come and go), with my more recent Bonkwave/Not Bonkwave tracks.
All those influences are merged into a coherent picture, vocal guitars going from 50s pop to modern day Chill Hop, folk rock and psychedelic rhythm guitar bleed into ambient textures.
I don’t often make music using anything other than guitar anymore, but when I do this is the sort of thing that comes out.
You can download lossless (higher quality audio) versions of these tracks from my website over here.

album.title: Endless (Journeyland Edition)
album.description:
In some respects everything ends, in others nothing does. It depends on your perspective. I wonder what is yours? Do you identify with this particular short span of life, or the seeming eternity of all the universes?
You don’t have to know where you’re going. There doesn’t have to be a purpose other than enjoying the ride and helping other people enjoy their ride.  The idea is to hold a mood or a thought or a colour for an amount of time and to be present.
Edited guitar improvisations over atmospheric drum beats become mind altering musical journeys along drone-like textures for soothing the soul over unimaginable timescales.

album.title: Rhythmic Booze
album.description:
"Rhythmic Booze" is a fun, upbeat album drenched in playful synthesizer melodies and toe-tapping beats. This collection of tracks combines the spirited energy of a night out with the colorful, whimsical sounds of synthesizers, creating a unique sonic experience that's both lively and charming. Each song in the album weaves a story of festivity, merriment, and a touch of mischievousness, reminiscent of the buzz and fizz of a good drink and great company.

     The album's essence is captured in its vibrant fusion of genres – from disco and electronica to hints of funk and retro pop – all brought to life through a modern synthesizer palette. Expect infectious rhythms, catchy hooks, and a feel-good vibe that persists from the first track to the last. "Rhythmic Booze" is perfect for those nights of uninhibited dancing or just grooving around the house, making it a must-listen for fans of fun, high-energy music with a playful twist.

tracks.title: The Ritalin Ramble
tracks.subtitle: The Ritalin Ramble
tracks.summary: "The Ritalin Ramble" is a high-energy techno track that combines pulsating rhythms with an undercurrent of frenetic, almost chaotic electronic melodies, emblematic of the frenzied yet focused energy often associated with its namesake. The song starts with a quick, gripping beat that instantly sets a tone of urgency and intensity. As the track unfolds, layers of synth interweave, creating a complex tapestry of sound that mirrors the cognitive rush of ideas and sensations. The core beat remains steadfast and driving, embodying a relentless pursuit of clarity amidst a whirlwind of thought and rhythm. The track is characterized by its rapid tempo, and a bassline that throbs like a heartbeat at the center of a digital jungle. The synthesizers dart in and out like quicksilver thoughts, at times converging into a harmonious melody before splintering into dissonant, yet captivating, soundscapes.

tracks.title: Disco Lasers
tracks.subtitle: Disco Lasers
tracks.summary: "Disco Lasers" is a vibrant and pulsating techno track that revives the glittering spirit of classic disco while infusing it with modern electronic energy. The song begins with a teasing, sparkling synth melody reminiscent of disco balls and neon lights, setting a stage that feels both nostalgic and freshly futuristic. The track quickly ramps up with a thumping, infectious beat that pays homage to the classic four-on-the-floor rhythm, quintessential to disco music. Layered atop are laser-like synth stabs and sweeps, cutting through the mix with precision and adding a dynamic, almost sci-fi quality to the tune. These "laser" sounds are not just accents but integral to the melody, creating a dazzling, rhythmic harmony that feels like dancing lights in a high-energy nightclub.

tracks.title: Baby Bed Bugs
tracks.subtitle: Baby Bed Bugs
tracks.summary: "Baby Bed Bugs" is an intriguing and whimsically titled synthesizer track that combines playful melodies with an undercurrent of mischievous electronic beats. This unique piece opens with a quirky, almost ticklish synthesizer riff that immediately sets a lighthearted and somewhat cheeky tone, invoking images of tiny creatures in a bustling, microscopic world. The track's core lies in its playful and catchy melody, which hums and buzzes around like its namesake, creating an environment that's both lively and slightly surreal. The synthesizer tones chosen are soft and rounded, with a bouncy quality that feels like a gentle, electronic lullaby infused with a sense of fun and frolic. Throughout "Baby Bed Bugs," there is a clever use of panning and stereo effects, making the sounds appear as if they are playfully scurrying from one ear to the other, echoing the skittering movements of little bugs. The rhythm is maintained by a series of crisp, clean beats and a deep, pulsating bassline that adds a sense of depth and warmth to the track, ensuring it maintains a foot-tapping groove despite its whimsical overtones.

tracks.title: Wonka and Winky
tracks.subtitle: Wonka and Winky
tracks.summary: "Wonka and Winky" is a playful, whimsical synthesizer track that instantly transports the listener to a world of imagination and fun. Inspired by the sounds and colors of a fantasy-filled adventure, the track begins with a flurry of bright, sparkling synth notes that dance and swirl with childlike wonder. The melody of "Wonka and Winky" is dynamic and captivating, featuring an array of electronic tones that mimic the playful mischief of its titular characters. Wonka's part of the melody is full of surprising twists and turns, akin to a whimsical inventor revealing one fantastical creation after another. In contrast, Winky's theme is more mischievous and impish, with playful staccatos and giggling arpeggios that suggest a cheeky, spirited personality. The rhythm section underpinning the track is light and buoyant, with bouncy beats and a pulsating bassline that add a joyful, toe-tapping energy. It's the kind of rhythm that encourages listeners to move and dance, perfectly capturing the essence of carefree, lighthearted play.

tracks.title: Pixelated Daydreams
tracks.subtitle: Pixelated Daydreams
tracks.summary: "Pixelated Daydreams" is a vibrant and captivating pop synthesizer track that marries nostalgic 8-bit sounds with modern pop rhythms, creating a blissful escape into a world of digital whimsy and colorful melodies. The song opens with a sequence of chiptune-inspired synth lines that instantly evoke a sense of retro gaming and youthful innocence, setting the tone for a journey through a bright, pixelated landscape of sound. The track’s structure follows a classic pop arrangement, with verse and chorus sections that are both catchy and emotionally resonant. The verses of "Pixelated Daydreams" are driven by a gentle, arpeggiated melody, where the synthesizer's voice is both tender and playful, suggesting a narrative of exploration and wonder. The pre-chorus builds with layers of harmonic textures, leading into an uplifting and infectious chorus. The chorus of "Pixelated Daydreams" bursts into an array of lush, warm synth pads and a rhythm that combines contemporary pop beats with the unmistakable charm of retro video game music. This section features a memorable, sing-along melody that feels both comforting and exhilarating – a soundtrack for daydreams where the digital and real worlds blend seamlessly

The core beat remains steadfast and driving, embodying a relentless pursuit of clarity amidst a whirlwind of thought and rhythm. The track is characterized by its rapid tempo, and a bassline that throbs like a heartbeat at the center of a digital jungle. The synthesizers dart in and out like quicksilver thoughts, at times converging into a harmonious melody before splintering into dissonant, yet captivating, soundscapes.

tracks.title: Blue Heron Pink Flamingo
tracks.summary:
Blue Heron - the cool bird that is so often hanging out at the creek. What a good Pennsylvania bird. And quite the singing voice! 

Pink Flamingo - the pink bird on the cans of Natural Lite "Naturdays" that my friend Billy and picked up on our pizza shop break to sip on while in the studio recording with Chelsea Lyn Meyer. 

Just felt like putting them in a song together.

tracks.title: Where There's a Will There's a Way
tracks.summary:
I really was learning how to write with my other hand at the time. I had wrist pain in my dominant hand and was giving it a rest.

My mom did always say "Can't means won't" a lot too. That stuck with me. 


Learning to write with my other hand
If I think I most certainly can
Mom always said, "can't mean's won't"
Why go about it same old same old?
As above, so  below
Mind will make what the heart sows

The sun is out behind the clouds
It's always clear
Who we need will always appear
Passion is key fly with the dove
A wise man travels with a compass of love

Go on ahead and rock the boat
Go on ahead and rock the boat
Go on ahead and rock the boat, OH!

This feeling inside is so hard to hide
And my heart has so much to say
Making my way at the end of the day
Where there's a will there's a way
Where there's a will there's a way
Where there's a will there's a way
Where there's a will there's a way

Lalalas...

tracks.title: Wild and Free
tracks.summary:
The title and song were inspired by a rear-mirror car ornament my talented sister-in-law, Erin, made for me. She's a fabulous artist!!! Check her out at http://ginsengalley.com/ or 
Erin also designed the Wild and Free album cover.

Distraction is there
At every turn
Dissonance, with some, you know
Everyone's a critic
Turn away, stay the course
And I'm my own worst critic
And the hardest to ignore

Watch me as I chase the light
The dream I had since I was a child
The secret to live wild and free
Be one with the one inside of me
Watch  me as I free the bind
And lift the weight and run like wild
The secret is be one with all
And live the dream
And love it all

First row seat
And I watch my life unfold
Head in Heaven, feet on the Earth

Of the greatest lessons I have learned
Practice hard, the Golden Rule
And give it all I have to give
and Love flows in return

Watch me as I chase the light
The dream I had since I was a child
The secret to live wild and free
Be one with the one inside of me
Watch  me as I free the bind
And lift the weight and run like wild
The secret is be one with all
And live the dream
And love it all

Shoo-be-doo-wop...

tracks.title: Dance With Me
tracks.summary:
This song was inspired by the Wine and Jazz Fest that my husband and I used to go for a few years in a row. It was so much fun wandering around and dancing in the great outdoors while listening to talented jazz artists, and sipping our wine from the tasting tents. It was a special time. We got engaged there in June 2013 and were married in October. 

Dance with me
Oh dance with me
Dance with me
Oh dance with me
Taste the wine on my lips
wrap your arms round my hips
let's sway, let's sway, let's sway, let's sway

Move like this
Bend and dip
Move like this
Bend and dip
Taste the wine on my lips
wrap your arms round my hips
let's sway, let's sway, let's sway, let's sway

Hold me close
Give it a go
Hold me so close
Give it ago
Taste the wine on my lips
wrap your arms round my hips
let's sway, let's sway, let's sway, let's sway

Dance with me
Oh dance with me
Dance with me
Oh dance with me
Taste the wine on my lips
wrap your arms round my hips
let's sway, let's sway, let's sway, let's sway
uh huh, uh huh...

tracks.title: Friends
tracks.summary:
Inspiration for this song came from being in two weddings in one day. One for two of my good friends from high school, and the other for my sister-in-law and brother-in-law. What a day! It was awesome. It went so smoothly, with little coordination and intervention on my part. One wedding happened to be earlier in the day, the other later, and I was able to wear the same dress to both since the brides chose the same color. It was meant to be all the way around. I was reflecting on how many beautiful, loving, people I am blessed to know and have known in my life, and just how many circles of family and friends I got to see all in one day!

Somehow I came to find you
I guess it was part of the plan
I'm glad I got to know you
I'm thankful you're my friend
Angel walking Earth
So much I have to learn
Hold my hand and walk with my, I'm listening
And oh,

If I never met you
I'm not sure where I'd be 
Little did you know, you came to rescue me
Whether in the good times, or whether in the bad
You helped create me, to make me who I am

People come and go
And some I haven't found
I'll be here with a smile to greet you if you come back around
And when it's time to go
And leave the big blue Earth
I wanna be somebody's angel
Be with them, birth to birth

If I never met you
I'm not sure where I'd be 
Little did you know, you came to rescue me
Whether in the good times, or whether in the bad
You helped create me, to make me who I am

We all make mistakes
We all lose control
Some much like each other
Forgive, look past it all

If I never met you
I'm not sure where I'd be 
Little did you know, you came to rescue me
Whether in the good times, or whether in the bad
You helped create me, to make me who I am

album.title: An Observed Earth
album.description:
Pastoral guitar in a modern age. Me in nature. Beyond veils, here I am in each moment letting the flow move me and the music.
These are highlights from Season Five of the podcast. I wanted to get back to playing without too much thought or structure and see what came out. One distinct style that appeared was kind of accoustic-based from a guitar sound point of view, but often effected with glitch delays and stutters as well as some flowing loops.
It seems to have a pastoral or nature theme which I’ve then reflected in the titles as meaningful imagery and botanical references that I think match up to the content. It reflects a slightly different approach and a new guitar to play with! Although it is different, it doesn’t vary wildly from what I do (after all, I don’t vary wildly at my core and through all of these that’s what I’ve been attemping to capture). So familiar, but different.
Visit Strange Textures for more information and music.  You can get lossless (higher quality audio) versions of my albums there to download and keep.

album.title: Heartland Captives
album.description:
Spur of the moment, flowing ambient guitar. Internal colours, shapes, and sensations. Me in myself.
These are highlights from Season Five of the podcast. I wanted to get back to playing without too much thought or structure and see what came out. These parts came together as a reflection of ‘the usual’ ambient improvisation but with a freer twist. They don’t venture too far from ambient guitar, but are looser than previous attempts.
They have that quality of revealing an inner state but remain connected to admittedly odd imagery based on real life. It’s a step away from nature, which happened in An Observed Earth and gives a glimpse further inside me. There feels like a connection with Marchland Stars here so the title reflects the link while the track titles refelct aspects of my mindset when creating them.
More information and music at Strange Textures.  You can get lossless (higher quality audio) versions of my albums there to download and keep.

tracks.title: Cocoon
tracks.summary: I was thinking of being cocooned and then emerging changed.  I wasn’t thinking of the film.  At all.

tracks.title: Inside Glass Hives
tracks.summary: I mean, I thought the hives were galss so you could see the bees buzzing.  But maybe they are glass bees too?

tracks.summary: You can just let go and float…

tracks.title: Web of the Ghost Spider
tracks.summary: Creepy thread-spinners

tracks.title: Enfolded (i)
tracks.summary: Decending, entering into somewhere dark.

album.summary:
Spur of the moment, flowing ambient guitar. Internal colours, shapes, and sensations. Me in myself.
These are highlights from Season Five of the podcast. I wanted to get back to playing without too much thought or structure and see what came out. These parts came together as a reflection of ‘the usual’ ambient improvisation but with a freer twist. They don’t venture too far from ambient guitar, but are looser than previous attempts.
They have that quality of revealing an inner state but remain connected to admittedly odd imagery based on real life. It’s a step away from nature, which happened in An Observed Earth and gives a glimpse further inside me. There feels like a connection with Marchland Stars here so the title reflects the link while the track titles refelct aspects of my mindset when creating them.
More information and music at Strange Textures.  You can get lossless (higher quality audio) versions of my albums there to download and keep.

feeds.title: Love In Its Purest Form
feeds.description:
Love In Its Purest Form is an audial onslaught of ethereal, synthesized, alternative, nocturnal melodies from the inner depths of your dreams, nightmares, realities and higher consciousness.
Written in my college dorm room and recorded between 2021 and 2023 through many trials and tribulations.
credits
released November 25, 2023
All sounds and lyrics written and recorded by Vance Latta.
Additional drum input provided by Kaden Latta.
Mixed and mastered by Kevin Carafa.

feeds.title: Lore and Legend
feeds.description: You saw them at LAUNCH on the Phantom Power Stage.  Dogbeach is an alt rock band from South Jersey that is approachable for all breeds of dogs, and sometimes cats with a variety of sounds that range from in your face to in your face. Dogbeach consists of Bob Maschio, Tyler Morales, Kevin Conrey, Johnny DeNicola, and the elusive Jim Maschio.

album.description:
This is the live album exclusive connected to the show - Into the Valueverse - Remember this is a value for value album and the artists have put it out for free, so if you enjoyed this record? please send them some value back with a message and tell them who you are and where you are listening from. Bitcoin prefered! All of the artists and crew are #V4V enabled and almost all the value sent will go directly to them. 

Presented by the New Music Nudge Unit, Into the Valueverse was a groundbreaking live music event held on Friday, 23rd May 2025 at The Fickle Pickle Club in Westcliff-on-Sea, Essex.

As the UK’s first-ever Bitcoin-powered gig, it fused cutting-edge technology with raw, independent sound in an unforgettable night of borderless, peer-to-peer performance.

Live Stream Sound & Video: @iNPC

Sound Engineer for the room: Joe Lamb

Host and Exec Producer: Aaron Dorn (Aaron of Essex)

🎤 Lineup:

Joe Martin – Americana storyteller with soul

Setlist:
1. Checkmate
2. My Heart Decided For Me
3. High Gravity
4. The Jetsons
5. Crocodile Tears
6. Empty Passenger Seat


Nathan Abbott – Bluesy Essex heart with a rock edge
Drums: Archie
Bass: Andy Carr

Setlist:
1. The Big I Am
2. Jenny
3. Into the Light
4. Upside Down
5. Looking Glass
6. 50 - 1
7. Sweet Sunshine

Longy – Southend rebel with electrifying punk-folk fire
Drums - @Tommydrums

Set list:
1. Heroes/Tape Up
2. Love Schizophrenia
3. Promise to my people
4. Back from the Abyss
5. Penthouses and Pavements
6. Careful What You Wish For 
7. Don't get me Started


To access the valueverse download a modern podcast app such as https://Fountain.fm or listen in via your browser using https://lnbeats.com or https://curiocaster.com

The valueverse is where artists publish their music to the Bitcoin layer of the internet, allowing fans and listeners to send “boosts” (small Bitcoin payments) directly to them. It’s music in its purest form: peer-to-peer, value-for-value. Artists receive almost all of the value, with no middlemen — just music, connection, and freedom. If you want to know more then message aaron @ newmusicnudgeunit@gmail.com

All photography provided by the awesome Raj - https://www.rajeshtaylor.com/into-the-valueverse-fickle-pickle-club-westcliff-on-sea 

Show was supported by the legends at https://AZTE.co - Get your bitcoin in seconds!
https://fountain.fm - The podcast app which is revolutionising how we listen.

https://bitcoinessex.co.uk - Getting everyone in the room!
https://headstarts.uk - Making the idea become a reality.

To access the valueverse download a modern podcast app such as https://Fountain.fm or listen in via your browser using https://lnbeats.com or https://curiocaster.com

The valueverse is where artists publish their music to the Bitcoin layer of the internet, allowing fans and listeners to send “boosts” (small Bitcoin payments) directly to them. It’s music in its purest form: peer-to-peer, value-for-value. Artists receive almost all of the value, with no middlemen — just music, connection, and freedom. If you want to know more then message aaron @ newmusicnudgeunit@gmail.com

All photography provided by the awesome Raj - https://www.rajeshtaylor.com/into-the-valueverse-fickle-pickle-club-westcliff-on-sea

tracks.title: Berserker
tracks.summary:
Denim Cobra's first single from the "Leather Diamond" EP, to be released in Fall 2023.

lyrics

Warships spotted from the shore

War cry from the Gjallarhorn

Terror in the eyes and hearts of men

Reaper's breath riding on the wind


Legends echoing

Through Odin's halls

Fearless fallen warriors

Enshrined in Valhalla


Gnashing teeth of the Warbeast

Bearskin armor on my back

Burning embers in my eyes and entrails

Raging in the blood of your ravaged soul


Legends echoing

Through Odin's halls

Fearless fallen warriors

Enshrined in Valhalla
credits
released March 1, 2023
Austin Bain aka Snake Fishskin: guitar/backing vocals

tracks.title: Slow Guillotine
tracks.summary:
Denim Cobra's second single from the "Leather Diamond" EP, to be released in Fall 2023.

lyrics

You face the punishment for your crimes
Today's the day that we sever your spine
Sentenced to suffer so it's gonna be slow
A dull blade, curated to corrode

Swift and humane is not the way
A crowd gathers to watch your neck spray
The blade struggles to release...
Godless infernal in a hellscape dream

No grease
Wrath of the torment machine
No priest
Last breath choking through broken teeth

Slow guillotine
Suffer severe

Slow torture
Dying in fear

Slow guillotine
Suffer severe

Spirit broken
Purgatory is near

Rust and flesh collide at last
Crushing weight, carotid artery smashed
The blade severs tendons one by one
Lamentations then rotting in the sun

Onlookers sick, forever scarred
Botched beheading, your body marred
The fifth hour of mutilation ends
The blade rises and falls again...

No grease
Wrath of the torment machine
No priest
Last breath choking through broken teeth

Slow guillotine
Suffer severe

Slow torture
Dying in fear

Slow guillotine
Suffer severe

Spirit broken
Purgatory is near
credits

tracks.title: Hermetic Drifter
tracks.summary:
Denim Cobra's third single from the "Leather Diamond" EP, to be released in Fall 2023.

lyrics

Hermetic Drifter
Highway is calling your name
On a blacked out pilgrimage
Cast out in exile again

The apparition has risen
Risen to guide the way

Premonitions and visions
Sacred incantations
Unearthing revelations
Cleansed by the cosmic light

Serpents wind
Shedding skins of your birthright
Sharpen your mind's eye
Inescapable fate

Shadowcaster
Threading your sights
Black widow crosshairs
Vanquish your mortal life

Nomadic Grifter
Desert is calling your name
God has forsaken his child
Baptized in a sea of flames

The alchemist's crucible
Flesh returning to dust again

Paradigm deviation
Eternal damnation
Waging war and annexation
Famine and fated desolation

Serpents wind
Shedding skins of your birthright
Sharpen your mind's eye
Inescapable fate

Shadowcaster
Threading your sights
Black widow crosshairs
Vanquish your mortal life

Threading your sights

Vanquish your mortal life

tracks.title: Sovereigns of the Air
tracks.summary:
Denim Cobra's fourth single from the "Leather Diamond" EP, to be released in Fall 2023.

lyrics

Rising from the mountains, to the river below
This frozen expanse is all I know

Ancient instincts driving
Fly in search of prey
Sharpened weapons dig in, and take you away

Sovereigns of the Air
Fate reigns from above
Forced eternal sleep
Now you're carrion

Nothing clouds my vision, gripping mortality
Bearing the burden
Keeping my bloodline alive

Thundering through the sky with a tear in my eye
We ride to glory, our spirit never dies

Sovereigns of the Air
Fate reigns from above
Forced eternal sleep
Now you're carrion

Sovereigns of the Air
Talons tearing up the sky
Forced eternal sleep
Now we carry on

feeds.title: That's The Spirit!
feeds.description:
This is The Retrograde's debut studio album with Cannabis Records. Their strong southern rock sound speaks towards life's everyday struggles. But through all of it, there is an undertone of hope, knowing that your hard work is getting you closer to something and one day it'll all come around. This album is packed with the sounds you love from the band you adore. It's sure to scratch that itch. Featuring their latest singles, I Need A Little, Closer to Somewhere and Come Around as well as an all new recording of their hit single, Dirty Daisy.

album.title: The Everyday
album.description:
This album represents nearly ten years of two great friends getting together once or twice a year to make music and have fun.
It’s been a long time since we played, as we live hours apart, and life gets in the way. That said, we have always experienced some awesome connection while jamming. To this day, we could probably hang out for a day or two, and an entire song (like the ones here) would come from it.
The first few songs on this album feature lyrics and vocals by The Everyday, while I took over the later songs after our brief recording sessions.
   
released May 13, 2022

"The Everyday"- vocals, guitar, piano
Ariel- drums, bass, keys, vocals, production.

feeds.title: deathdreams
feeds.description:
'deathdreams' was written and performed by Emily Whitehurst, the solo artist behind Survival Guide. Produced and recorded by Bob Hoag in late 2022 at Flying Blanket Studios in Mesa, AZ.

At times a darkly sonic and emotional hand grenade and others a poppy shimmering rainbow of rich melodies and textures, 'deathdreams' is a tour de force that showcases the depth of Whitehurst’s songwriting, lyrical imagery, and vocal fortitude. Far-ranging in its topic matter, the album touches on the themes of anxiety, the power of cinema, and the dangers of societal influences, in addition to Whitehurst’s dreams about dying.

tracks.title: Bad Little Seed
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

Place cards, centerpiece
She asks me what she did wrong
How disappointing
Gave it away for a song
Sticky floor, sticky beer
Smells like cigarettes here
Surrounded by dirty men
And I’d do it all again

Get out of this town and see the world
Take your life and do what you prefer
Get out of this town, go see the world
Breaking the rules and your heart
How did us girls ever turn out this way?
Breaking the rules and your heart

You gave us courage, you gave us strength
You taught us girls can do anything
We don’t have to wear the white dress standing at the altar
If we don’t want to now
Do you regret it all?
Wish you’d kept your words small?
I’m on my own road
Where it ends up, I don’t know

CHORUS

Joy won’t shelter you
You can’t eat your dreams
What a bad little seed
Who just wanted to be free

CHORUS

tracks.title: Sour Sorrow
tracks.summary:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

It’s so embarrassing to admit that I still feel sick
When our song comes on the radio
Flavor’s bitter like vinegar but you’ve been with her
For ages now, I know
I’m so tired of pining over you
If there was something I could do, I would do it

Parting is such sour sorrow
The taste you left with me
It’s a real tough pill to swallow
So hard to believe that it’s just 
Sour sorrow
Sour sorrow, now it’s just
Sour sorrow
When will this feeling leave?

I used to think I was oh so strong
I was never wrong
Never let a man get me down
Salty memories make my skin burn
When will I learn to forget you now?
I’m so ashamed that I can’t be happy for you
If there was something I could do, I could do, I would do, I would do it

CHORUS

I told myself so long ago

album.summary:
'deathdreams' was written and performed by Emily Whitehurst, the solo artist behind Survival Guide. Produced and recorded by Bob Hoag in late 2022 at Flying Blanket Studios in Mesa, AZ.

At times a darkly sonic and emotional hand grenade and others a poppy shimmering rainbow of rich melodies and textures, 'deathdreams' is a tour de force that showcases the depth of Whitehurst’s songwriting, lyrical imagery, and vocal fortitude. Far-ranging in its topic matter, the album touches on the themes of anxiety, the power of cinema, and the dangers of societal influences, in addition to Whitehurst’s dreams about dying.

feeds.title: Home Sweet Home (The Dream of Love Survives but it Disappoints Constantly)
feeds.description: As you press play on "Home Sweet Home (The Dream of Love Survives but it Disappoints Constantly)," the opening notes of the electronic instrumental album send a shiver down your spine. The haunting melodies and dissonant harmonies seem to echo through the empty spaces of a world long forgotten, evoking images of a desolate landscape where hope and happiness are distant memories. The album's electronic instrumentation is both eerie and ethereal, capturing the shattered and broken nature of a dystopian world in a hauntingly beautiful way. The persistent dream of love that survives, but disappoints constantly, is a poignant reminder...

album.title: Home Sweet Home (The Dream of Love Survives but it Disappoints Constantly)
album.description: As you press play on "Home Sweet Home (The Dream of Love Survives but it Disappoints Constantly)," the opening notes of the electronic instrumental album send a shiver down your spine. The haunting melodies and dissonant harmonies seem to echo through the empty spaces of a world long forgotten, evoking images of a desolate landscape where hope and happiness are distant memories. The album's electronic instrumentation is both eerie and ethereal, capturing the shattered and broken nature of a dystopian world in a hauntingly beautiful way. The persistent dream of love that survives, but disappoints constantly, is a poignant reminder of the fragility of human emotion and the power of hope in the face of adversity. This album is a powerful reflection on the human condition, a warning of what can happen when we neglect to nurture the things that truly matter in life, and a call to fight for a better future where love and hope can once again flourish in a world that has been left to decay.

feeds.title: Beware of Banjo
feeds.description:
In 2008, I locked myself in A room with a banjo and this is what came out. This is NOT typical, out of tune, twangy banjo music. I would say this is relaxing, acoustic, instrumental music. I made this as a solo project while performing with The Doerfels, the band I started with four of my younger brothers and our only sister. 
Anyways, If you dare to listen, Beware of Banjo!
If you receive any value from this music, which I loved making, please let me know with any kind of value! ITM TYFYC KTLD,
Sir TJ The Wrathful
